    RangeDimension

    Dimension descriptor for a dimension that is irregularly sampled.

    The RangeDimension covers cases when indexes of a dimension are mapped to other values in a not regular fashion. A use-case for this would be for example irregularly sampled time-series or certain kinds of histograms. To achieve the mapping of the indexes an array of mapping values must be provided. Those values are stored in the dimensions setTicks(double[]) property. In analogy to the sampled dimension a setUnit(String) and a setLabel(String) can be defined.

    See Also:
    Dimension, SampledDimension, SetDimension
